description: Circular MIL Spec Backshells Straight Shell size 25 Black Zinc Nickel w/ Exposed Nickel Entry 2
info:
Backshells
        
        
            Amphenol Pcd Backshells offer strain relief, environmental protection, and 360° EMI/RFI shielding at the termination area of virtually any circular connector. These connectors feature a base material constructed of aluminum alloy, stainless steel, brass, or composite and a variety of finishes such as black zinc nickel, cadmium, electroless nickel, anodized black, passivated, and more. Amphenol Pcd Backshells have custom designs available and meet or exceed RoHS/REACH compliance standards. Available in both military specifications and commercial types for any application, these backshells meet the Society of Automotive Engineers (SAE) AS85049 standard.

description: Circular MIL Spec Connector Receptacle, solder, 5 contacts
Circular MIL Spec Connector Receptacle, Crimp, 7 contacts
info:
VG Circular Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Air LB Germany VG Circular Connectors operate over a wide temperature range (as low as -65°C and up to +175°C) and are designed for harsh environments. The VG Circular Connectors include the GCB-B series, PT round plug connectors, and the SJT round plug connectors. The GCB-B connectors offer reverse bayonet locking (according to VG95234), high reliability, and are waterproof as well as wear- and vibration-resistant. The PT round plug connectors with bayonet locking are approved as per VG95328, MIL26482 Series I for crimp, solder, single solder, and wire-wrap contacts. An HF-sealed version is also available. Scoop-proof SJT round plug connectors with reverse bayonet locking are approved per VG96912, PAN6433-2, JN 1003.

description: Circular MIL Spec Connector 3 POS RADSOK 8 STRAIGHT PLUG
info:
RADSOK® Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Industrial RADSOK® Connectors upgrade many core connectors by simply adding the RADSOK advantage. RADial SOcKet (RADSOK) is a socket cylinder within a female contact that has several equally spaced longitudinal beams twisted into a hyperbolic shape. As the male pin is inserted, axial members in the female half deflect, imparting high current flow across the connection with minimal voltage loss. The configuration ensures a large, coaxial, face-to-face surface area engagement and is ideal for crimp termination applications requiring repeated mating cycles and high current with a low millivolt drop. Amphenol connectors using RADSOK technology include Amphe-GTR Reverse Bayonet Connectors for Power Applications, PowerBus Amphe-PD™ Connectors, Amphe-Power® Connectors, board level connectors such as PowerBlok™, RADSERT™, and PGY™, SurLok Connectors, and Helios H4 Solar Connectors.

description: Circular MIL Spec Connector Plug, 10-6, Skt Zinc Nickel
info:
Gray Zinc Nickel (ZnNi) Circular Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Industrial Gray Zinc Nickel (ZnNi) Circular Connectors feature cadmium-free, RoHS-compliant plating that is suitable for harsh environments. These ZnNi-plated connectors are originally developed for harsh marine environments and feature a -65°C to +200°C temperature range and withstand 500 hours of salt spray. These connectors offer <2.5mΩ conductivity and consist of gray zinc over an electroless nickel base, giving the connector a light gunmetal gray appearance. This plating delivers high corrosion resistance and has no significant galvanic reaction when mated with leading standard-market plating options.

description: Circular MIL Spec Connector PLUG, METAL, GRAY ZNNI, 11-2 SOCKET
info:
Amphe-Lite M3 Circular MIL-Spec Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Industrial Amphe-Lite M3 Circular MIL-Spec Connectors are designed to obtain metal-to-metal coupling for superior EMI shielding capability. Amphe-Lite Metal is 100% scoop-proof and features high-density contact arrangements. This Amphenol Industrial connector series provides self-locking, quick disconnect threaded coupling as well as locksmith keying. The five key-way polarization of these connectors provides five alternate rotations. This circular connector series also features corrosion resistance. Shells of Gray ZnNi playing can withstand a 500-hour salt spray exposure. Moisture resistance through an improved interfacial seal design prevents electrolytic erosion of contacts.

description: Circular MIL Spec Connector CONN PLUG ST 13POS W/SCKT
info:
MIL-DTL-38999 Series III Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol MIL-DTL-38999 Series III Circular Connectors deliver high-performance capabilities for demanding general duty and harsh environment applications. Developed to operate under severe high temperature and vibration, the connectors feature rapid coupling via a Tri-Start™ thread, shell-to-shell, or metal-to-metal bottoming. Amphenol designed these connectors to provide an EMI shielding capability of 65dB minimum at 10GHz and corrosion resistance of up to 500-hour salt spray exposure. Amphenol MIL-DTL-38999 Series III Circular Connectors offer a rated current range of 1.5A to 5A, a temperature range of -65°C to +175°C, minimum insulation resistance of 5000MΩ, and a dielectric withstanding voltage of 1000VRMS. These rugged and highly reliable circular connectors are ideally suited for industrial, commercial air, military, C4ISR, and space applications.

description: Circular MIL Spec Connector 8P Sz 16 Socket Plug Strt Strain Relief
info:
PT 26482 Series 1 Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Industrial PT 26482 Series 1 Connectors are miniature cylindrical connectors offering twice the number of contacts in half the size of a standard connector. These miniature bayonet connectors are available in solder contact, high performance crimp, and commercial crimp versions. Both the solder contact and high performance crimp versions meet all MIL-DTL-26482 Series 1 requirements. Amphenol Industrial PT 26482 Series 1 Connectors are ideally suited for use in commercial, military, and aerospace industries.

description: Circular MIL Spec Connector STINGRAY-7FEM IDC WALL MNT
info:
Stingray Magnetic Connectors & Harnesses
        
        
            Amphenol LTD Stingray Magnetic Connectors and Harnesses are low-profile, compact sealed connectors that withstand exposure to rain, dust, dirt, and chemicals. This series is designed for use by first responders, security, and military personnel. The magnetic, non-keyed mating system allows the connectors to be easily mated without the need for pre-alignment and eliminates the need to operate any coupling mechanisms. The low-profile connector lays flat against the body to prevent snagging and damage, while the strong magnetic connection makes it self-aligning and allows flexibility in cable routing. Amphenol LTD Stingray Magnetic Connectors and Harnesses are optimized for USB 2.0 protocols and are an ideal solution for audio, power, or data signals.

            Amphenol Industrial AC Threaded Industrial Cylindrical Connectors are a commercial derivative of the MIL-DTL-5015 product used in military and industrial applications. info:
MIL-DTL-38999 Series III Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol MIL-DTL-38999 Series III Circular Connectors deliver high-performance capabilities for demanding general duty and harsh environment applications. Developed to operate under severe high temperature and vibration, the connectors feature rapid coupling via a Tri-Start™ thread, shell-to-shell, or metal-to-metal bottoming. Amphenol designed these connectors to provide an EMI shielding capability of 65dB minimum at 10GHz and corrosion resistance of up to 500-hour salt spray exposure. These rugged and highly reliable circular connectors are ideally suited for industrial, commercial air, military, C4ISR, and space applications.

description: Circular MIL Spec Connector Power connector dedicated to user safety derived from MIL-DTL 38999 Series III Size 17
info:
PowerSafe MIL-DTL-38999 Series III Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Socapex PowerSafe MIL-DTL-38999 Series III Connectors were developed to transfer high power (500V) in harsh environments with full safety for the user. The circular connectors offer an IP28 rating, tested pressure watertight (48h, under 2m water), and allows a finger test for socket contacts and inserts. Depending on the shell and backshell plating option, the PowerSafe connectors operate in a temperature range as low as -65°C and up to +200°C. The Amphenol Socapex PowerSafe MIL-DTL-38999 Series III Connectors are ideal for use in defense, avionics, and harsh industrial markets.

description: Circular MIL Spec Connector CONNECTOR, PLASTIC, REAR MOUNT, SQUARE RECEPTACLE, LESS CONTACTS, 18-11, 5 POLE, PIN, ROHS
info:
APC Circular Plastic Shell Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Industrial APC Circular Plastic Shell Connectors have a 3-start ACME thread and 2-way bayonet design for fast coupling. These lightweight, corrosion-resistant connectors feature a robust design for rugged environments and are durable to 500 mating cycles. This connector series is ROHS compliant, can withstand current up to 30A, and has an insulation resistance of 500M at 500VDC. The connectors feature a self-locking mechanism and are rated at IP67 when mated. APC Connectors also comply with UL 94 V-0 flammability and are UV resistant and F1-rated. Amphenol Industrial APC Circular Plastic Shell Connectors are designed for use in various applications, including industrial machinery, agricultural machinery, factory automation, materials handling equipment, communications equipment, HVAC, lighting and signage, and rail and transit vehicles and systems.

info:
Gray Zinc Nickel (ZnNi) Circular Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Industrial Gray Zinc Nickel (ZnNi) Circular Connectors feature cadmium-free, RoHS-compliant plating that is suitable for harsh environments. These ZnNi-plated connectors are originally developed for harsh marine environments and feature a -65°C to +200°C temperature range and withstand 500 hours of salt spray. These connectors offer <2.5mΩ conductivity and consist of gray zinc over an electroless nickel base, giving the connector a light gunmetal gray appearance. This plating delivers high corrosion resistance and has no significant galvanic reaction when mated with leading standard-market plating options.

info:
5015 Series Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Industrial 5015 Series Connectors are rugged and versatile. These environmentally resistant connectors offer proven electrical capability for a cost-effective solution. The medium to heavyweight cylindrical 5015 connectors are available in a range of shell styles, shell sizes, and service classes. They are designed to MIL-DTL-5015 (SAE-AS50151) standards. description: Circular MIL Spec Connector Jam Nut Recpt Nickel plate
info:
Amphe-Lite M3 Circular MIL-Spec Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Industrial Amphe-Lite M3 Circular MIL-Spec Connectors are designed to obtain metal-to-metal coupling for superior EMI shielding capability. Amphe-Lite Metal is 100% scoop-proof and features high-density contact arrangements. This Amphenol Industrial connector series provides self-locking, quick disconnect threaded coupling as well as locksmith keying. The five key-way polarization of these connectors provides five alternate rotations. This circular connector series also features corrosion resistance. Shells of Gray ZnNi playing can withstand a 500-hour salt spray exposure. Moisture resistance through an improved interfacial seal design prevents electrolytic erosion of contacts.

description: Circular MIL Spec Connector 6P PLG SZ 17 SKT CBL MNT
info:
MIL-DTL-38999 Series III Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol MIL-DTL-38999 Series III Circular Connectors deliver high-performance capabilities for demanding general duty and harsh environment applications. Developed to operate under severe high temperature and vibration, the connectors feature rapid coupling via a Tri-Start™ thread, shell-to-shell, or metal-to-metal bottoming. Amphenol designed these connectors to provide an EMI shielding capability of 65dB minimum at 10GHz and corrosion resistance of up to 500-hour salt spray exposure. Amphenol MIL-DTL-38999 Series III Circular Connectors offer a rated current range of 1.5A to 5A, a temperature range of -65°C to +175°C, minimum insulation resistance of 5000MΩ, and a dielectric withstanding voltage of 1000VRMS. These rugged and highly reliable circular connectors are ideally suited for industrial, commercial air, military, C4ISR, and space applications.

info:
Backshell Clamps
        
        
            Amphenol Pcd Backshell Clamps help to tidy up the cable after termination and provide strain relief at the termination area. The clamps are offered in environmental and non-environmental options, as well as EMI/RFI. The components are available in black zinc nickel, adding to the existing finishes in olive drab gray cadmium, tin, or nickel with a variety of shell sizes 11 through 48. Amphenol Pcd Backshell Clamps meet MIL-DTL-38999, MIL-DTL-26482 Series II, MIL-DTL-83723 Series I and II, MIL-DTL-24308, and MIL-DTL-83513.

description: Circular MIL Spec Connector MS/TRI-START HERMETIC
info:
Hermetic Circular Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Aerospace Hermetic Circular Connectors maintain system integrity in applications where reliability and performance are critical, such as gas-tight barriers or areas with high-pressure differentials. A wide range of materials and manufacturing capabilities are used to provide consumer and MIL-Spec products for glass-to-metal seals and lightweight epoxy backfilled solutions. The epoxy-sealed connectors are a lightweight alternative to glass-sealed hermetic connectors for use in avionics and other weight-sensitive applications where a high level of sealing is required. Epoxy-sealed connectors are an optimal solution when increasingly stringent sealing requirements must be met.

These connectors utilize the last mate, first break sequence due to the available interlock circuitry and accommodate standard MIL-DTL-38999 accessories. Amphenol Aerospace High Voltage 38999-Style Circular Connectors are ideal for military and defense applications.

description: Circular MIL Spec Contacts Quadrax Socket conta ct, 100?, 1000 Base-
info:
HS Amphe-Lite Circular MIL-Spec Contacts
        
        
            Amphenol Industrial HS Amphe-Lite Circular MIL-Spec Contacts incorporates high-speed contacts into Amphe-Lite housing, providing datalink solutions. The Amphe-Lite offers high-data transfer rates, excellent EMI compatibility, and lower power consumption rates. These connectors are available in Differential Quadrax Contacts and Split Pair Quadrax Contacts variants. The Amphe-Lite connectors are designed for high-speed signal applications in ruggedized and high vibration environments. This includes two pairs (4 pins) of high-speed contacts having bandwidth up to 3.125GHz, Ethernet Bas-T-100Ω, and a data rate of up to 6.5Gbps. The Amphe-Lite Quadrax features rear-release contacts, front and rear mount, and EMI- shielding. These connectors come with two Ohm matched impedance differential pairs, available in size 8 crimp termination or PC trails. The Amphe-Lite circular MIL-Spec contacts require modification of the MIL-DTL-38999 connector to accommodate keyed contacts.

            TE Connectivity's Polamco Swept Elbow Backshells are designed with a smooth internal bore and a continuous bend radius. info:
VG Circular Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Air LB Germany VG Circular Connectors operate over a wide temperature range (as low as -65°C and up to +175°C) and are designed for harsh environments. The VG Circular Connectors include the GCB-B series, PT round plug connectors, and the SJT round plug connectors. The GCB-B connectors offer reverse bayonet locking (according to VG95234), high reliability, and are waterproof as well as wear- and vibration-resistant. The PT round plug connectors with bayonet locking are approved as per VG95328, MIL26482 Series I for crimp, solder, single solder, and wire-wrap contacts. An HF-sealed version is also available. Scoop-proof SJT round plug connectors with reverse bayonet locking are approved per VG96912, PAN6433-2, JN 1003.

info:
RNJ Rack & Panel Cylindrical Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Socapex RNJ Rack and Panel Cylindrical Connectors connect electrical and optical devices between a moving unit (rack) and a fixed unit (panel) without any coupling/uncoupling device. This function is ensured by a system of moving and fixed units. Amphenol Socapex RNJ Rack and Panel Connectors are derived from the LJT series and meet or exceed MIL-DTL-38999 Series I requirements. The RNJ series is qualified for the requirements of the standard DAT C 5935 x 0005 HE308 21, 25, 26, and 27T models.

Available in both military specifications and commercial types for any application, these backshells meet the Society of Automotive Engineers (SAE) AS85049 standard.

info:
MIL-DTL-38999 Series III Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol MIL-DTL-38999 Series III Circular Connectors deliver high-performance capabilities for demanding general duty and harsh environment applications. Developed to operate under severe high temperature and vibration, the connectors feature rapid coupling via a Tri-Start™ thread, shell-to-shell, or metal-to-metal bottoming. Amphenol designed these connectors to provide an EMI shielding capability of 65dB minimum at 10GHz and corrosion resistance of up to 500-hour salt spray exposure. Amphenol MIL-DTL-38999 Series III Circular Connectors offer a rated current range of 1.5A to 5A, a temperature range of -65°C to +175°C, minimum insulation resistance of 5000MΩ, and a dielectric withstanding voltage of 1000VRMS. These rugged and highly reliable circular connectors are ideally suited for industrial, commercial air, military, C4ISR, and space applications.

info:
Class L Commercial MIL-DTL-22992 Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Aerospace Heavy Duty Class L Commercial MIL-DTL-22992 Connectors are a commercial version of the heavy-duty power connectors needed for rugged environmental conditions. These cost-effective connectors feature MIL-DTL-22992 Class L insert arrangements and an arc quenching design, which protects users and equipment if connectors are inadvertently disconnected under load. A programmed coupling sequence ensures grounding and neutral contacts engage before power contacts. Amphenol Aerospace Heavy Duty Class L Commercial MIL-DTL-22992 Connectors are constructed using high-strength aluminum and a unique combination of grommets and seals. These rugged connectors provide waterproofing in any condition, including mated or unmated, capped, or uncapped.

            Amphenol Air LB Germany Electrically Conductive Gaskets offer a comprehensive range of electrically conductive gaskets for receptacles and accessories. These electrically conductive gaskets range includes all variants from the VG96940-6. The series features fluorosilicone and a homogeneous mixture of conductive materials such as silver-coated aluminum particles (Version A) or nickel-carbon-particles (Version B). Amphenol Air LB Germany Electrically Conductive Gaskets provide maximum protection against moisture, dirt, and are resistant to aggressive fluids such as oil, hydraulic, or kerosene. VG Circular Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Air LB Germany VG Circular Connectors operate over a wide temperature range (as low as -65°C and up to +175°C) and are designed for harsh environments. The VG Circular Connectors include the GCB-B series, PT round plug connectors, and the SJT round plug connectors. The GCB-B connectors offer reverse bayonet locking (according to VG95234), high reliability, and are waterproof as well as wear- and vibration-resistant. The PT round plug connectors with bayonet locking are approved as per VG95328, MIL26482 Series I for crimp, solder, single solder, and wire-wrap contacts. An HF-sealed version is also available. Scoop-proof SJT round plug connectors with reverse bayonet locking are approved per VG96912, PAN6433-2, JN 1003.

description: Circular MIL Spec Connector RNJ Plug 26 NI sz 17 rot N 17-35 insert
info:
RNJ Rack & Panel Cylindrical Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Socapex RNJ Rack and Panel Cylindrical Connectors connect electrical and optical devices between a moving unit (rack) and a fixed unit (panel) without any coupling/uncoupling device. This function is ensured by a system of moving and fixed units. Amphenol Socapex RNJ Rack and Panel Connectors are derived from the LJT series and meet or exceed MIL-DTL-38999 Series I requirements. The RNJ series is qualified for the requirements of the standard DAT C 5935 x 0005 HE308 21, 25, 26, and 27T models.

description: Circular MIL Spec Backshells Straight Shell size 14 Black Zinc Nickel w/ Exposed Nickel Entry 2
info:
Backshells
        
        
            Amphenol Pcd Backshells offer strain relief, environmental protection, and 360° EMI/RFI shielding at the termination area of virtually any circular connector. These connectors feature a base material constructed of aluminum alloy, stainless steel, brass, or composite and a variety of finishes such as black zinc nickel, cadmium, electroless nickel, anodized black, passivated, and more. Amphenol Pcd Backshells have custom designs available and meet or exceed RoHS/REACH compliance standards. Available in both military specifications and commercial types for any application, these backshells meet the Society of Automotive Engineers (SAE) AS85049 standard.

description: Circular MIL Spec Connector TV PLUGS - DURMALON
info:
Durmalon & AP93 Heavy Duty Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Aerospace Durmalon and AP93 Heavy Duty MIL-DTL-22992 Connectors offer a 40A to 100A current range, 120VAC to 480VAC voltage, and 28, 32, 44, and 52 shell sizes. These heavy duty connectors are a part of the Class "L" series and meet the demand for heavy duty and heavy power connectors that are critical for rugged environmental conditions. The Durmalon finish provides protection against 500 hours of dynamic salt spray, while the AP-93 plating exceeds 1000 hour salt spray requirements. Amphenol Aerospace Durmalon AP93 Heavy Duty Connectors feature a rugged, waterproof design and a programmed coupling sequence.

description: Circular MIL Spec Connector 4 PIN CONTACT CABLE MOUNT PLUG
info:
MW Series MIL-DTL-55181 Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Pcd MW Series MIL-DTL-55181 Connectors are ideal for military and harsh environments. The waterproof and polarized connectors feature a center lock coupling screw, ensuring the ability to withstand high shock and vibration. These connectors require minimal finger space for mating, allowing closer board configuration than other mil-spec connectors. Amphenol Pcd MW Series connectors are typically used for the interconnection of power and control including military communication equipment and ground vehicles.

description: Circular MIL Spec Connector 2P Shell Size 16S Straight Plug
info:
5015 Series Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Industrial 5015 Series Connectors are rugged and versatile. These environmentally resistant connectors offer proven electrical capability for a cost-effective solution. The medium to heavyweight cylindrical 5015 connectors are available in a range of shell styles, shell sizes, and service classes. They are designed to MIL-DTL-5015 (SAE-AS50151) standards. Amphenol Industrial 5015 Connectors offer more than 300 insert patterns and are available with solder or crimp contacts as well as RADSOK® contacts in certain sub-series.

description: Circular MIL Spec Tools, Hardware & Accessories WATERPROOF CAP 1.0P M CONN SCREW
info:
M Series Sensor Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol LTW M Series Sensor Connectors feature waterproof ratings of IP65, IP67, and IP68 with current ratings of 1.5A to 28A. This connector series includes receptacles, connectors overmolded with cable, and field-installable connectors with >100 mating cycles. Amphenol LTW M Series Sensor Connectors meet IEC 61076-2-101 and IEC 61076-2-104 standards. They come in standard cable lengths ranging from 1m to 99m and are also available in M8 SMT and M12 SMT variants.

description: Circular MIL Spec Connector 5015 REAR RELEASE ALUMINUM ASSEMBLY
info:
Amphenol MIL-Circular Connectors
            
            
                Amphenol Aerospace's extensive line of MIL-circular connectors come in many different sizes and configurations. Mouser offers this comprehensive line of circular connectors fully assembled and in-stock. Having our stock fully assembled enables your connectors to ship same-day, so you can have the right connector right now.

description: Circular MIL Spec Connector 100P Sz 23 Straight Plug Nickel
info:
MIL-DTL-38999 Series III Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol MIL-DTL-38999 Series III Circular Connectors deliver high-performance capabilities for demanding general duty and harsh environment applications. Developed to operate under severe high temperature and vibration, the connectors feature rapid coupling via a Tri-Start™ thread, shell-to-shell, or metal-to-metal bottoming. Amphenol designed these connectors to provide an EMI shielding capability of 65dB minimum at 10GHz and corrosion resistance of up to 500-hour salt spray exposure. Amphenol MIL-DTL-38999 Series III Circular Connectors offer a rated current range of 1.5A to 5A, a temperature range of -65°C to +175°C, minimum insulation resistance of 5000MΩ, and a dielectric withstanding voltage of 1000VRMS. These rugged and highly reliable circular connectors are ideally suited for industrial, commercial air, military, C4ISR, and space applications.

description: Circular MIL Spec Connector 10P Size 12 Pin Plug Strt Strain Relief
info:
PT 26482 Series 1 Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Industrial PT 26482 Series 1 Connectors are miniature cylindrical connectors offering twice the number of contacts in half the size of a standard connector. These miniature bayonet connectors are available in solder contact, high performance crimp, and commercial crimp versions. Both the solder contact and high performance crimp versions meet all MIL-DTL-26482 Series 1 requirements. Amphenol Industrial PT 26482 Series 1 Connectors are ideally suited for use in commercial, military, and aerospace industries.

description: Circular MIL Spec Tools, Hardware & Accessories sealing gasket,conductive,65sh, bright- size n
info:
Electrically Conductive Gaskets
        
        
            Amphenol Air LB Germany Electrically Conductive Gaskets offer a comprehensive range of electrically conductive gaskets for receptacles and accessories. These electrically conductive gaskets range includes all variants from the VG96940-6. The series features fluorosilicone and a homogeneous mixture of conductive materials such as silver-coated aluminum particles (Version A) or nickel-carbon-particles (Version B). Amphenol Air LB Germany Electrically Conductive Gaskets provide maximum protection against moisture, dirt, and are resistant to aggressive fluids such as oil, hydraulic, or kerosene. Typical applications of electrically conductive gaskets include military, aerospace, and industrial applications.

            Amphenol Socapex CapLocks and PlugLocks are locking systems that prevent access to critical connectors by intrusion or human error. These are locking accessories for MIL-DTL-38999 series III, RJFTV, and USBFTV connectors. CapLocks are locking rings that allow a cap to lock onto a receptacle to secure the port access. Once locked, they can turn freely around a cap and prevent fingers from unlocking the cap. PlugLocks are locking rings that allow a plug to lock onto a receptacle to secure the plug-to-receptacle connection. These locks can turn freely once locked around the plug coupling unit, preventing fingers from unlocking the mated pair.

description: Circular MIL Spec Backshells Straight Shell size 17 Black Zinc Nickel w/ Exposed Nickel Entry 3
info:
Backshells
        
        
            Amphenol Pcd Backshells offer strain relief, environmental protection, and 360° EMI/RFI shielding at the termination area of virtually any circular connector. These connectors feature a base material constructed of aluminum alloy, stainless steel, brass, or composite and a variety of finishes such as black zinc nickel, cadmium, electroless nickel, anodized black, passivated, and more. Amphenol Pcd Backshells have custom designs available and meet or exceed RoHS/REACH compliance standards. Available in both military specifications and commercial types for any application, these backshells meet the Society of Automotive Engineers (SAE) AS85049 standard.

Product Category: Circular MIL Spec Tools, Hardware & Accessories
Product Type: Circular MIL Spec Tools, Hardware & Accessories
description: Circular MIL Spec Tools, Hardware & Accessories sealing gasket,conductive,65sh, bright- size n
info:
VG Circular Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Air LB Germany VG Circular Connectors operate over a wide temperature range (as low as -65°C and up to +175°C) and are designed for harsh environments. The VG Circular Connectors include the GCB-B series, PT round plug connectors, and the SJT round plug connectors. The GCB-B connectors offer reverse bayonet locking (according to VG95234), high reliability, and are waterproof as well as wear- and vibration-resistant. The PT round plug connectors with bayonet locking are approved as per VG95328, MIL26482 Series I for crimp, solder, single solder, and wire-wrap contacts. An HF-sealed version is also available. Scoop-proof SJT round plug connectors with reverse bayonet locking are approved per VG96912, PAN6433-2, JN 1003.

Product Type: Circular MIL Spec Tools, Hardware & Accessories
description: Circular MIL Spec Tools, Hardware & Accessories sealing gasket,conductive,65sh, bright- size n
info:
Electrically Conductive Gaskets
        
        
            Amphenol Air LB Germany Electrically Conductive Gaskets offer a comprehensive range of electrically conductive gaskets for receptacles and accessories. These electrically conductive gaskets range includes all variants from the VG96940-6. The series features fluorosilicone and a homogeneous mixture of conductive materials such as silver-coated aluminum particles (Version A) or nickel-carbon-particles (Version B). Amphenol Air LB Germany Electrically Conductive Gaskets provide maximum protection against moisture, dirt, and are resistant to aggressive fluids such as oil, hydraulic, or kerosene. Typical applications of electrically conductive gaskets include military, aerospace, and industrial applications.

description: Circular MIL Spec Tools, Hardware & Accessories CAP, CPC, SIZE 23 RECP, BLACK
info:
Circular Plastic Connectors (CPC) Protective Caps
        
        
            TE Connectivity's Circular Plastic Connectors (CPC) Protective Caps are designed to fit the existing CPC plugs and receptacles, providing protection from environmental contaminants. These protective caps are disposable, recyclable, and feature up to 80°C temperature resistance. The CPC protective caps are available in orange, red, black, and yellow colors. These protective caps are used in robotics, industrial machinery, instrumentation, power supplies, material handling, and welding equipment.

description: Circular MIL Spec Connector 2M805 PC TAILS
info:
2M Warrior Grip Push-Pull Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Aerospace 2M Warrior Grip Push-Pull Connectors combine fast charging, 10A capability, and compatibility to existing Nett Warrior Push-Pull Connectors. Amphenol Aerospace 2M Warrior Grip Push-Pull Connectors offer numerous enhancements to the standard 2M804 design, including a unique mate-force rating for quick disconnect and selectively plated shells for improved conductivity. The Warrior Grip is tailor-made for nearly any soldier-worn application.

description: Circular MIL Spec Connector TV PLUGS - DURMALON
info:
Durmalon & AP93 Heavy Duty Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Aerospace Durmalon and AP93 Heavy Duty MIL-DTL-22992 Connectors offer a 40A to 100A current range, 120VAC to 480VAC voltage, and 28, 32, 44, and 52 shell sizes. These heavy duty connectors are a part of the Class "L" series and meet the demand for heavy duty and heavy power connectors that are critical for rugged environmental conditions. The Durmalon finish provides protection against 500 hours of dynamic salt spray, while the AP-93 plating exceeds 1000 hour salt spray requirements. Amphenol Aerospace Durmalon AP93 Heavy Duty Connectors feature a rugged, waterproof design and a programmed coupling sequence.

description: Circular MIL Spec Connector
info:
D38999 Series III Double Flange Receptacles
        
        
            ITT Cannon D38999 Series III Double Flange Receptacles for PCB mounting are engineered for use in high-vibration, harsh environment applications across the aerospace and defense industry. These robust connectors can attach directly to the connector shell, which improves grounding, reduces contact solder joint stress, and eliminates extra hardware. ITT Cannon D38999 Double Flange Receptacles feature 500 mating cycles and an operating temperature range of -65°C to +200°C. These components offer convenience, performance, and reliability, making them ideal for military aviation, ground transports, commercial aerospace, and communications systems.

Mil-Spec Circular Connectors - 38999 & 26482
        
        
            Souriau Mil-Spec Circular Connectors 38999 Series I, II, III & 26482 Series I & II offer a complete range of standard and derived circular connectors for harsh environments. info:
VG Circular Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Air LB Germany VG Circular Connectors operate over a wide temperature range (as low as -65°C and up to +175°C) and are designed for harsh environments. The VG Circular Connectors include the GCB-B series, PT round plug connectors, and the SJT round plug connectors. The GCB-B connectors offer reverse bayonet locking (according to VG95234), high reliability, and are waterproof as well as wear- and vibration-resistant. The PT round plug connectors with bayonet locking are approved as per VG95328, MIL26482 Series I for crimp, solder, single solder, and wire-wrap contacts. An HF-sealed version is also available. Scoop-proof SJT round plug connectors with reverse bayonet locking are approved per VG96912, PAN6433-2, JN 1003.

description: Circular MIL Spec Backshells Straight Shell size 25 Black Zinc Nickel w/ Exposed Nickel Entry 3
info:
Backshells
        
        
            Amphenol Pcd Backshells offer strain relief, environmental protection, and 360° EMI/RFI shielding at the termination area of virtually any circular connector. These connectors feature a base material constructed of aluminum alloy, stainless steel, brass, or composite and a variety of finishes such as black zinc nickel, cadmium, electroless nickel, anodized black, passivated, and more. Amphenol Pcd Backshells have custom designs available and meet or exceed RoHS/REACH compliance standards. Available in both military specifications and commercial types for any application, these backshells meet the Society of Automotive Engineers (SAE) AS85049 standard.

info:
Mil/Aero MD801 Circular Connectors
        
        
            Cinch Mil/Aero MD801 Circular Connectors are designed to deliver reliable performance that is equal to MIL-DTL-38999. These plugs and receptacles feature crimp contacts, dual-start ACME thread, banding platform, and size 9 shell with aluminum / nickel PTFE finish. The connectors use a standard interface and can mate with Amphenol 2M series and Glenair 801 series. Cinch Mil/Aero MD801 connectors offer full performance in extreme environments, making them well-suited for military, medical, and downhole applications.

info:
Durmalon & AP93 Heavy Duty Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Aerospace Durmalon and AP93 Heavy Duty MIL-DTL-22992 Connectors offer a 40A to 100A current range, 120VAC to 480VAC voltage, and 28, 32, 44, and 52 shell sizes. These heavy duty connectors are a part of the Class "L" series and meet the demand for heavy duty and heavy power connectors that are critical for rugged environmental conditions. The Durmalon finish provides protection against 500 hours of dynamic salt spray, while the AP-93 plating exceeds 1000 hour salt spray requirements. Amphenol Aerospace Durmalon AP93 Heavy Duty Connectors feature a rugged, waterproof design and a programmed coupling sequence.

description: Circular MIL Spec Tools, Hardware & Accessories sealing gasket,conductive,75sh, dark size n
info:
Electrically Conductive Gaskets
        
        
            Amphenol Air LB Germany Electrically Conductive Gaskets offer a comprehensive range of electrically conductive gaskets for receptacles and accessories. These electrically conductive gaskets range includes all variants from the VG96940-6. The series features fluorosilicone and a homogeneous mixture of conductive materials such as silver-coated aluminum particles (Version A) or nickel-carbon-particles (Version B). Amphenol Air LB Germany Electrically Conductive Gaskets provide maximum protection against moisture, dirt, and are resistant to aggressive fluids such as oil, hydraulic, or kerosene. Typical applications of electrically conductive gaskets include military, aerospace, and industrial applications.

info:
C90 Circular Connectors
        
        
            Harwin C90 Circular Connectors are intermateable with MIL-DTL-5015 and offer full environmental sealing with the use of backshells and sealing gaskets (exceeds IP67). This low-cost, highly durable, and rugged connector system offers a 22AWG to 16AWG wire size, 13A current rating, and -55°C to +125°C operating temperature range. The connectors feature solder termination, threaded and polarized coupling, and zinc and black chromate-plated shells. Harwin C90 Circular Connectors are ideal for use in industrial, oil and gas, agricultural, construction, harsh environments, and rail / transportation applications.

description: Circular MIL Spec Backshells BACKSHELL NON ENV EMI/RFI ST NIC SZ 16
info:
Backshell Clamps
        
        
            Amphenol Pcd Backshell Clamps help to tidy up the cable after termination and provide strain relief at the termination area. The clamps are offered in environmental and non-environmental options, as well as EMI/RFI. The components are available in black zinc nickel, adding to the existing finishes in olive drab gray cadmium, tin, or nickel with a variety of shell sizes 11 through 48. Amphenol Pcd Backshell Clamps meet MIL-DTL-38999, MIL-DTL-26482 Series II, MIL-DTL-83723 Series I and II, MIL-DTL-24308, and MIL-DTL-83513.

description: Circular MIL Spec Connector 3P Sz 14S Box Mount Pin Recept Solder
info:
97 Series Cylindrical Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Industrial General Duty Standard 97 Series Cylindrical Connectors provide a cost-effective solution utilizing the proven MIL-C-5015 style. These connectors are versatile and offer a large selection of insert patterns. The 97 series features a threaded coupling, hard dielectric inserts, six shell options with 128 different contact arrangements, and 1 to 52 circuits. The connectors are fabricated from high-grade aluminum alloy and are UL and CSA recognized. RoHS versions are available with 946 suffixes. Amphenol Industrial General Duty Standard 97 Series Cylindrical Connectors are widely used for the automotive, robotics, machine tool, and welding industries, as well as in other commercial applications.

Circular MIL Spec Contacts 8P Socket use W/ Cbl PIC E6A3824
info:
Octonet Contacts
        
        
            Amphenol Aerospace Octonet Contacts feature eight strategically spaced inner contacts that form 100Ω matched impedance differential pairs. This superior Ethernet contact system is designed for MIL-DTL-38999 Series III connectors. The Octonet series is 10G Ethernet compliant and meets the performance specifications of CAT-6A cables. The contacts are available in a size 8 crimp termination style and can be installed in existing size 8 Quadrax cavities. Amphenol Aerospace Octonet Contacts are ideal for military and commercial air avionics as well as high-speed Ethernet applications.

description: Circular MIL Spec Connector 3P PLG SZ 9 SKT CBL MNT
info:
MIL-DTL-38999 Series III Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol MIL-DTL-38999 Series III Circular Connectors deliver high-performance capabilities for demanding general duty and harsh environment applications. Developed to operate under severe high temperature and vibration, the connectors feature rapid coupling via a Tri-Start™ thread, shell-to-shell, or metal-to-metal bottoming. Amphenol designed these connectors to provide an EMI shielding capability of 65dB minimum at 10GHz and corrosion resistance of up to 500-hour salt spray exposure. Amphenol MIL-DTL-38999 Series III Circular Connectors offer a rated current range of 1.5A to 5A, a temperature range of -65°C to +175°C, minimum insulation resistance of 5000MΩ, and a dielectric withstanding voltage of 1000VRMS. These rugged and highly reliable circular connectors are ideally suited for industrial, commercial air, military, C4ISR, and space applications.

Circular MIL Spec Connector HERMETIC
info:
Hermetic Circular Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Aerospace Hermetic Circular Connectors maintain system integrity in applications where reliability and performance are critical, such as gas-tight barriers or areas with high-pressure differentials. A wide range of materials and manufacturing capabilities are used to provide consumer and MIL-Spec products for glass-to-metal seals and lightweight epoxy backfilled solutions. The epoxy-sealed connectors are a lightweight alternative to glass-sealed hermetic connectors for use in avionics and other weight-sensitive applications where a high level of sealing is required. Epoxy-sealed connectors are an optimal solution when increasingly stringent sealing requirements must be met.

description: Circular MIL Spec Connector High Speed 2M801 Plu kel, Anti-Decoupling
info:
2M Micro-Miniature Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Aerospace 2M Micro-Miniature Connectors are designed for interconnect applications requiring high performance. These connectors are 71% lighter, 52% smaller, and have 60% more contact density than other connectors in their class. These micro-miniature connectors are designed and tested to Mil-Spec standards and comparable to MIL-DTL-38999 connectors. They are offered in four types: triple-start ACME thread, push-pull, bayonet, and dual-start ACME thread. Amphenol Aerospace 2M Micro-Miniature Connectors are intermountable and intermateable with existing micro-miniature aerospace/defense connectors, including the Glenair Mighty Mouse series. These lightweight, high-density connectors maximize SWaP (size, weight, and power) in a variety of high-reliability, harsh environments.

These next-generation connectors offer weight and space savings while exceeding the performance of D38999. Amphenol Aerospace Series Five Black Zinc-Nickel Circular Connectors use 38999-qualified components and are rated at higher voltages, providing designers with an optimal solution. Applications include military / defense, aerospace, harsh environments, and general duty.

description: Circular MIL Spec Connector Recept. Crimp 13cts 10GBit
info:
TV Data Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Air LB Germany TV Data Connectors are MIL-DTL-38999 Series III connectors featuring EMI/RFI protection and high corrosion resistance. These connectors come in nine shell sizes (from 09 to 25) with more than 80 contact arrangements. The TV data connectors feature high-density inserts that are compatible with twinax, coax, and quadrax and the receptacles come with reinforced sealing. The shell material of these connectors are made of Aluminum, stainless steel, and marine bronze. The stainless steel sheet material provides firewall capability and the marine bronze shell provides robustness for marine applications. The TV data connectors plating are made of olive drab cadmium, nickel, passivation, and black zinc nickel. These connectors are capable of quick coupling with mate and self-lock in a 360° turn of the coupling nut and anti-decoupling device for high vibration performance. The EMI/RFI protection is available via shell-to-shell bottoming and grounding fingers on the plug shell.

info:

            Amphenol Industrial APC Circular Plastic Shell Connectors have a 3-start ACME thread and 2-way bayonet design for fast coupling. These lightweight, corrosion-resistant connectors feature a robust design for rugged environments and are durable to 500 mating cycles. This connector series is ROHS compliant, can withstand current up to 30A, and has an insulation resistance of 500M at 500VDC. The connectors feature a self-locking mechanism and are rated at IP67 when mated. APC Connectors also comply with UL 94 V-0 flammability and are UV resistant and F1-rated. Amphenol Industrial APC Circular Plastic Shell Connectors are designed for use in various applications, including industrial machinery, agricultural machinery, factory automation, materials handling equipment, communications equipment, HVAC, lighting and signage, and rail and transit vehicles and systems.

info:

A wide range of materials and manufacturing capabilities are used to provide consumer and MIL-Spec products for glass-to-metal seals and lightweight epoxy backfilled solutions. Epoxy-sealed connectors are an optimal solution when increasingly stringent sealing requirements must be met.

            Amphenol MIL-DTL-38999 Series III Circular Connectors deliver high-performance capabilities for demanding general duty and harsh environment applications. Developed to operate under severe high temperature and vibration, the connectors feature rapid coupling via a Tri-Start™ thread, shell-to-shell, or metal-to-metal bottoming. Amphenol designed these connectors to provide an EMI shielding capability of 65dB minimum at 10GHz and corrosion resistance of up to 500-hour salt spray exposure. Amphenol MIL-DTL-38999 Series III Circular Connectors offer a rated current range of 1.5A to 5A, a temperature range of -65°C to +175°C, minimum insulation resistance of 5000MΩ, and a dielectric withstanding voltage of 1000VRMS. These rugged and highly reliable circular connectors are ideally suited for industrial, commercial air, military, C4ISR, and space applications.

info:
Black-Zinc Nickel-Finish Backshell Clamps
        
        
            Amphenol Pcd Black-Zinc Nickel-Finish Backshell Clamps are a RoHS compliant replacement for cadmium plating. The black-zinc, nickel-finish clamps are a cost-effective cable holding option over cadmium and offer environmental protection. The series is available in a variety of shell sizes (11 through 48), both military (MIL) specification and commercial types, and with EMI/RFI shielding. The clamps clean-up the cable after termination and provide good strain relief at the termination area. Amphenol Pcd Black Zinc Nickel Finish Backshell Clamps are can be used as a replacement for cadmium plating in aeronautical and military applications.

description: Circular MIL Spec Connector CONNECTOR, PLASTIC, REAR MOUNT, SQUARE RECEPTACLE, LESS CONTACTS, 18-4, 4 POLE, PIN, ROHS
info:
APC Circular Plastic Shell Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Industrial APC Circular Plastic Shell Connectors have a 3-start ACME thread and 2-way bayonet design for fast coupling. These lightweight, corrosion-resistant connectors feature a robust design for rugged environments and are durable to 500 mating cycles. This connector series is ROHS compliant, can withstand current up to 30A, and has an insulation resistance of 500M at 500VDC. The connectors feature a self-locking mechanism and are rated at IP67 when mated. APC Connectors also comply with UL 94 V-0 flammability and are UV resistant and F1-rated. Amphenol Industrial APC Circular Plastic Shell Connectors are designed for use in various applications, including industrial machinery, agricultural machinery, factory automation, materials handling equipment, communications equipment, HVAC, lighting and signage, and rail and transit vehicles and systems.

Developed to operate under severe high temperature and vibration, the connectors feature rapid coupling via a Tri-Start™ thread, shell-to-shell, or metal-to-metal bottoming. Amphenol designed these connectors to provide an EMI shielding capability of 65dB minimum at 10GHz and corrosion resistance of up to 500-hour salt spray exposure. Amphenol MIL-DTL-38999 Series III Circular Connectors offer a rated current range of 1.5A to 5A, a temperature range of -65°C to +175°C, minimum insulation resistance of 5000MΩ, and a dielectric withstanding voltage of 1000VRMS. These rugged and highly reliable circular connectors are ideally suited for industrial, commercial air, military, C4ISR, and space applications.

info:
VG Circular Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Air LB Germany VG Circular Connectors operate over a wide temperature range (as low as -65°C and up to +175°C) and are designed for harsh environments. The VG Circular Connectors include the GCB-B series, PT round plug connectors, and the SJT round plug connectors. The GCB-B connectors offer reverse bayonet locking (according to VG95234), high reliability, and are waterproof as well as wear- and vibration-resistant. The PT round plug connectors with bayonet locking are approved as per VG95328, MIL26482 Series I for crimp, solder, single solder, and wire-wrap contacts. An HF-sealed version is also available. Scoop-proof SJT round plug connectors with reverse bayonet locking are approved per VG96912, PAN6433-2, JN 1003.

info:
DuraMate™ AHDP Circular Plastic Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Sine Systems DuraMate™ AHDP Circular Plastic Connectors are environmentally sealed, heavy-duty, circular connectors. This series provides an economical, quick-connect, bayonet locking system that is manufactured to withstand the challenges and complexities of off-road harsh environment applications. These connectors are available in size 24 with 13 insert arrangements and in size 18 with 6 insert arrangements. The connectors feature an easy-grip coupling system with visual and tactile indicators that ensure reliable mating confirmation. Two different backshell systems thread onto the rear of the connectors to provide strain relief and additional wire seal protection. Amphenol Sine Systems DuraMate AHDP connectors offer IP68 / IP69K protection (in mated condition) from dust, water, mud, and other contaminants. The AHDP components are ideal for panel-mount or in-line heavy-duty applications such as commercial vehicles, agriculture, construction, and marine installations.

info:

            Amphenol Air LB Germany VG Circular Connectors operate over a wide temperature range (as low as -65°C and up to +175°C) and are designed for harsh environments. The VG Circular Connectors include the GCB-B series, PT round plug connectors, and the SJT round plug connectors. description: Circular MIL Spec Strain Reliefs & Adapters Strain Relief Clamp
info:
Black-Zinc Nickel-Finish Backshell Clamps
        
        
            Amphenol Pcd Black-Zinc Nickel-Finish Backshell Clamps are a RoHS compliant replacement for cadmium plating. The black-zinc, nickel-finish clamps are a cost-effective cable holding option over cadmium and offer environmental protection. The series is available in a variety of shell sizes (11 through 48), both military (MIL) specification and commercial types, and with EMI/RFI shielding. The clamps clean-up the cable after termination and provide good strain relief at the termination area. Amphenol Pcd Black Zinc Nickel Finish Backshell Clamps are can be used as a replacement for cadmium plating in aeronautical and military applications.

description: Circular MIL Spec Connector plug Crimp 6Pin
info:
GCA/GCB/VG95234 Circular MIL Spec Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Air LB Germany GCA/GCB/VG95234 Circular MIL Spec Connectors feature reverse bayonet or threaded coupling, a nickel surface, and solder contacts. The reverse bayonet coupling and an ondular washer guarantee fast and effortless locking/unlocking and avoid an unintentional unlatch due to heavy vibrations. The connectors offer high liability and use the same installation dimensions and contact arrangements as MIL-C-5015 connectors. These components are also coevally waterproof and resistant to vibrations and wear. Common applications include industrial plants and railway vehicles as well as propulsion technologies, machine tools, measurement, and robotics.

description: Circular MIL Spec Connector CATALOG CONNECTORS/COMPONENTS
info:
Tri-Power Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Aerospace Tri-Power Connectors combine the reliability of MIL-DTL-38999 III Tri-Start Connectors with high-current RADSOK and Temper-Grip contacts. Amphenol Aerospace Tri-Power Connectors enable users to choose contacts ranging from 70A to 250A per contact (240A to 1000A per connector). The series enables more current-carrying capability than comparably-sized MIL-DTL-5015 and MIL-DTL-22992 connectors. Tri-Power Connectors with RADSOK offer low contact engagement / separation force, low contact resistance, and silver-plated contacts. Tri-Power Connectors with Temper-Grip handle up to +200°C with no decrease in performance and provide gold-plated contacts.

description: Circular MIL Spec Connector PT CARBON STEEL HERMETIC & MINOR MODS
info:
Hermetic Circular Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Aerospace Hermetic Circular Connectors maintain system integrity in applications where reliability and performance are critical, such as gas-tight barriers or areas with high-pressure differentials. A wide range of materials and manufacturing capabilities are used to provide consumer and MIL-Spec products for glass-to-metal seals and lightweight epoxy backfilled solutions. The epoxy-sealed connectors are a lightweight alternative to glass-sealed hermetic connectors for use in avionics and other weight-sensitive applications where a high level of sealing is required. Epoxy-sealed connectors are an optimal solution when increasingly stringent sealing requirements must be met.
